Sentencas: Direct utilization of methanol in liquid tin anode solid oxide fuel cells has been experimentally demonstrated at 1023 K. A Cu and SDC modified Sn anode solid oxide fuel cell had a maximum power density of 259.2 mW/cm(2) during operation on methanol.
Titulo: Direct methanol utilization in intermediate temperature liquid-tin anode solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Carbon deposition was not observed in the Raman spectra of the post-test anodes.
Titulo: Direct methanol utilization in intermediate temperature liquid-tin anode solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy indicated that gas conversion resistance increased when using methanol instead of hydrogen.
Titulo: Direct methanol utilization in intermediate temperature liquid-tin anode solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The micro-channel architecture of the electrode mitigated the increase.
Titulo: Direct methanol utilization in intermediate temperature liquid-tin anode solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy images showed that addition of Cu and Sn improved wetting of Sn on YSZ and reduced anode polarization resistance.
Titulo: Direct methanol utilization in intermediate temperature liquid-tin anode solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode gases were analyzed by mass spectroscopy and a mechanism for electrochemical oxidation of methanol has been proposed.
